message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper discusses a cellular automata-based approach for the segmentation of vertebral bodies using magnetic resonance imaging. This involves image analysis and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on medical imaging and neurosurgery, which are relevant to the sub-categories of medical imaging (cs.MED) and neuronal and cognitive systems (cs.NEURON).
